goals.question: What is the relationship between population and hurricanes in each state?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['population'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different states?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['hurricanes'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency of Hurricanes')
    plt.title('What is the frequency of hurricanes in each state?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['engineers'], bins=10, color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Engineers')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engineers across different states?')
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
